  "prompt": "How is WhatsApp able to show the blurred image even after deleting the original copy from the gallery?",
  "response": "WhatsApp's ability to show a blurred image even after the original copy has been deleted from the gallery is due to how it handles media caching and temporary storage. Here's a breakdown of the process:\n\n1. **Media Download**: When you receive an image on WhatsApp, the app typically downloads the media and stores it temporarily in a cache folder on your device. This allows the app to display the image quickly without needing to re-download it every time you view it.\n\n2. **Blurred Preview**: WhatsApp generates a lower-resolution, blurred version of the image (or a thumbnail) for preview purposes. This is a common practice to save data and provide a quick visual reference without loading the full-resolution image immediately.\n\n3. **Cached Data**: The blurred version of the image is often stored in the app's cache or temporary storage. This means that even if the original image is deleted from your gallery or the \"WhatsApp Images\" folder, the cached, low-resolution version may still be accessible within the app.\n\n4. **App-Specific Storage**: WhatsApp stores media and its associated previews in its own directory, separate from the gallery. Deleting the original image from the gallery does not always remove the cached or temporary files stored by WhatsApp.\n\n5. **File Management**: To completely remove all traces of an image, including the blurred preview, you may need to clear WhatsApp's cache or delete the image from within the app itself (e.g., by deleting the chat or clearing media files in WhatsApp settings).\n\n### How to Clear the Blurred Image:\n- **Clear Cache**: Go to your device's settings > Apps > WhatsApp > Storage > Clear Cache. This will remove temporary files, including blurred previews.\n- **Delete Media in WhatsApp**: Open WhatsApp, go to the chat containing the image, and delete the media file directly from the chat.\n- **Clear Storage**: In extreme cases, you can clear WhatsApp's storage (via the same path as clearing cache), but this will remove all media and data related to WhatsApp.\n\nBy understanding this mechanism, you can better manage what WhatsApp stores and how to fully remove media from your device.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
